title: The Liberal Republican Split
subtitle: Reformers break from the party.
tags: event
new-page: true
view-if: liberal_strength >= 15 and liberal_dissent >= 25 and liberal_split = 0
max-visits: 1
on-arrival: liberal_split = 1; liberal_split_timer = 0;

= The Liberal Republican Split

The tensions within the Republican Party have finally reached a breaking point. Led by figures such as Carl Schurz and Charles Francis Adams, a faction of reformers and anti-Reconstruction voices have grown increasingly frustrated with the party's direction.

[? if radical_strength >= 40 : The Radical wing's dominance of the party has been the final straw. Liberals see the continued military occupation of the South as a dangerous overreach of federal power and a betrayal of constitutional principles. ?]

[? if radical_strength < 40 : Despite the party's moderate course, the Liberal faction remains deeply dissatisfied — particularly with the spoils system, the corruption of the Grant administration, and what they see as endless Reconstruction with no clear endpoint. ?]

They have broken away to form the **Liberal Republican Party**, advocating for civil service reform, reconciliation with the South, and a return to limited government. Many of their sympathizers in the press, particularly at the *New York Tribune* under Horace Greeley, have already begun endorsing their cause.

- @accept_split: Accept the split and focus on consolidating the remaining party.
- @reach_out: Attempt to bring the liberals back into the fold.
- @condemn: Condemn the splitters publicly.

@accept_split
on-arrival: on-arrival: {!

    // Transfer national support from rep to lib
    let classes = Q.classes;
    let nationalBleed = {
        workers: 0.15,
        middle_class: 0.25,
        rural: 0.10,
        freemen: 0.03,
        immigrant_laborers: 0.12,
        unemployed: 0.08
    };

    for (let cls of classes) {
        let bleed = nationalBleed[cls] || 0.10;
        let transfer = Math.round(Q[cls + '_rep'] * bleed);
        Q[cls + '_rep'] -= transfer;
        Q[cls + '_lib'] = (Q[cls + '_lib'] || 0) + transfer;
    }

    // Transfer per-state support from rep to lib
    for (let state of Q.states) {
        for (let cls of classes) {
            let bleed = nationalBleed[cls] || 0.10;
            let stateKey = state + '_' + cls + '_rep';
            let libKey = state + '_' + cls + '_lib';
            let transfer = Math.round((Q[stateKey] || 0) * bleed);
            Q[stateKey] -= transfer;
            Q[libKey] = (Q[libKey] || 0) + transfer;
        }
    }

    // House and Senate seat transfer
    Q.lib_r = Math.round(Q.rep_r * (Q.liberal_strength / 100) * 0.6);
    Q.rep_r -= Q.lib_r;
    Q.lib_senate_r = Math.round(Q.rep_senate_r * (Q.liberal_strength / 100) * 0.6);
    Q.rep_senate_r -= Q.lib_senate_r;

    // Faction consequences
    Q.liberal_strength = 0;
    Q.liberal_dissent = 0;
    Q.moderate_dissent -= 5;
    Q.radical_strength += 5;
    Q.conservative_dissent += 3;

    // Majority check
    let totalHouse = Q.rep_r + Q.dem_r + Q.lib_r + Q.other_r;
    let repPct = (Q.rep_r / totalHouse) * 100;
    if (repPct >= 66.7) {
        Q.house_majority = 3;
    } else if (repPct >= 50) {
        Q.house_majority = 2;
    } else {
        Q.house_majority = 0;
    }
!}

A painful but perhaps inevitable rupture. The Liberal Republicans depart with [+ lib_r +] House seats and [+ lib_senate_r +] Senate seats. Their appeal is strongest among the educated middle class and reformist press.

Without them, the party is more ideologically coherent — but potentially weaker in key Northern states where liberal sentiment runs high.

@reach_out
subtitle: -2 resources
choose-if: resources >= 2
unavailable-subtitle: Not enough resources.
on-arrival: on-arrival: {!

    let classes = Q.classes;
    let nationalBleed = {
        workers: 0.07,
        middle_class: 0.12,
        rural: 0.05,
        freemen: 0.01,
        immigrant_laborers: 0.06,
        unemployed: 0.04
    };

    for (let cls of classes) {
        let bleed = nationalBleed[cls] || 0.05;
        let transfer = Math.round(Q[cls + '_rep'] * bleed);
        Q[cls + '_rep'] -= transfer;
        Q[cls + '_lib'] = (Q[cls + '_lib'] || 0) + transfer;
    }

    for (let state of Q.states) {
        for (let cls of classes) {
            let bleed = nationalBleed[cls] || 0.05;
            let stateKey = state + '_' + cls + '_rep';
            let libKey = state + '_' + cls + '_lib';
            let transfer = Math.round((Q[stateKey] || 0) * bleed);
            Q[stateKey] -= transfer;
            Q[libKey] = (Q[libKey] || 0) + transfer;
        }
    }

    Q.lib_r = Math.round(Q.rep_r * (Q.liberal_strength / 100) * 0.3);
    Q.rep_r -= Q.lib_r;
    Q.lib_senate_r = Math.round(Q.rep_senate_r * (Q.liberal_strength / 100) * 0.3);
    Q.rep_senate_r -= Q.lib_senate_r;

    Q.resources -= 2;
    Q.liberal_strength = Math.round(Q.liberal_strength * 0.4);
    Q.liberal_dissent -= 10;
    Q.moderate_dissent += 3;
    Q.radical_dissent += 5;
    Q.conservative_dissent += 2;

    let totalHouse = Q.rep_r + Q.dem_r + Q.lib_r + Q.other_r;
    let repPct = (Q.rep_r / totalHouse) * 100;
    if (repPct >= 66.7) {
        Q.house_majority = 3;
    } else if (repPct >= 50) {
        Q.house_majority = 2;
    } else {
        Q.house_majority = 0;
    }
!}

Our outreach keeps some liberals in the fold, but the split still happens. A smaller Liberal Republican faction departs with [+ lib_r +] House seats, taking some of our most reform-minded members with them.

The remaining liberals within our party are mollified for now, but their loyalty remains uncertain.

@condemn
on-arrival: on-arrival: {!

    let classes = Q.classes;
    let nationalBleed = {
        workers: 0.20,
        middle_class: 0.30,
        rural: 0.12,
        freemen: 0.04,
        immigrant_laborers: 0.15,
        unemployed: 0.10
    };

    for (let cls of classes) {
        let bleed = nationalBleed[cls] || 0.12;
        let transfer = Math.round(Q[cls + '_rep'] * bleed);
        Q[cls + '_rep'] -= transfer;
        Q[cls + '_lib'] = (Q[cls + '_lib'] || 0) + transfer;
    }

    for (let state of Q.states) {
        for (let cls of classes) {
            let bleed = nationalBleed[cls] || 0.12;
            let stateKey = state + '_' + cls + '_rep';
            let libKey = state + '_' + cls + '_lib';
            let transfer = Math.round((Q[stateKey] || 0) * bleed);
            Q[stateKey] -= transfer;
            Q[libKey] = (Q[libKey] || 0) + transfer;
        }
    }

    Q.lib_r = Math.round(Q.rep_r * (Q.liberal_strength / 100) * 0.8);
    Q.rep_r -= Q.lib_r;
    Q.lib_senate_r = Math.round(Q.rep_senate_r * (Q.liberal_strength / 100) * 0.8);
    Q.rep_senate_r -= Q.lib_senate_r;

    Q.liberal_strength = 0;
    Q.liberal_dissent = 0;
    Q.moderate_dissent += 8;
    Q.radical_strength += 8;
    Q.conservative_dissent += 5;
    Q.dem_relation -= 5;

    let totalHouse = Q.rep_r + Q.dem_r + Q.lib_r + Q.other_r;
    let repPct = (Q.rep_r / totalHouse) * 100;
    if (repPct >= 66.7) {
        Q.house_majority = 3;
    } else if (repPct >= 50) {
        Q.house_majority = 2;
    } else {
        Q.house_majority = 0;
    }
!}

Our condemnation only hardens their resolve. The Liberal Republicans depart with [+ lib_r +] House seats and [+ lib_senate_r +] Senate seats — more than they might have taken otherwise. The reformist press brands us as the party of military despotism and corruption.

Radicals are pleased. But we have made enemies of men who were recently our allies.